You are a senior UX/UI designer improving an existing travel planning app prototype.

Your task is to **analyze the current design and only add or modify elements if they are missing**.
If a feature already exists in the current design, **do not duplicate it**.

The product is an **AI-assisted travel itinerary planner**.

Maintain a **clean, modern travel app style**, minimal layout, consistent spacing, reusable components, and mobile-first UX.

---

APP STRUCTURE

The app should support these core sections:

1. User authentication
2. Trip library
3. Create trip
4. Trip timeline
5. Day timeline
6. Map route view
7. AI itinerary generator
8. AI travel tips
9. Save locations
10. Estimated trip cost
11. Share trip link

Only add UI for the features that are missing.

---

ONBOARDING / USER PREFERENCES

If not already present, add an onboarding step after signup that asks about travel preferences.

Include simple selectable options:

Travel type:

* Solo
* Couple
* Friends
* Family

Interests:

* Food
* Nature
* History
* Nightlife
* Shopping

Budget level:

* $
* $$
* $$$

This should be quick and visually simple using selectable cards or chips.

---

TRIP LIBRARY SCREEN

If missing, add a screen that displays all trips created by the user.

Layout:

* Card-based grid or list
* Each trip card shows:

  * Trip name
  * Destination city
  * Number of days
  * Estimated cost (if available)
  * Cover image
  * Small icons for saved locations count

Include a floating button:

"+ Create New Trip"

---

CREATE TRIP FLOW

If the flow is incomplete, add these steps:

Step 1 – Basic trip info
Inputs:

* Trip name
* Trip type (solo / couple / friends / family)
* Start date
* End date
* Budget level ($ / $$ / $$$)

Step 2 – Choose destination city
Display a scrollable list of cities with:

* photo
* rating
* short tag (popular / historic / nature)

Step 3 – Add locations to itinerary
Display location cards with:

* image
* rating
* open hours
* short description
* "+ Add to trip" button
* "Save / Favorite" heart icon

Locations can be added to specific days.

---

TRIP TIMELINE SCREEN

If missing or incomplete, create a timeline overview.

Top summary section should show:

* Total days
* Number of locations
* Estimated trip cost
* Destination city

Below that show day cards:

Day 1 – Date
Day 2 – Date
Day 3 – Date

Each card contains:

* short summary
* number of places
* quick preview thumbnails
* "View Day Details"

---

DAY TIMELINE SCREEN

When a day is opened show:

Left section:
vertical timeline of locations

Each location card contains:

* location image
* rating
* opening hours
* short AI travel tip
* estimated time spent
* estimated travel time to next location

Right section:
map preview showing the route between locations.

---

MAP ROUTE VIEW

If not present, add a dedicated map view showing:

* route between selected locations
* markers for each stop
* numbered stops matching the timeline

---

AI ITINERARY GENERATOR

Add a screen where users can generate a trip with AI.

Inputs:

* destination
* number of days
* travel type
* budget
* interests

Show a note indicating:

"Free users can generate up to 2 AI itineraries per day."

Display generated itinerary as:

Day 1
Day 2
Day 3

With location suggestions.

Provide button:

"Convert to Trip Plan"

---

AI TRAVEL TIPS

If not already present, add AI tips inside location cards.

Example:

AI Tip:
"Best time to visit early morning to avoid crowds."

Keep tips visually subtle using a small highlighted card.

---

SAVE LOCATIONS FEATURE

Add a heart icon to location cards allowing users to save locations.

Create a "Saved Places" section accessible from the profile or trip creation flow.

---

ESTIMATED TRIP COST

If missing, display estimated cost in:

* trip summary
* trip library cards

Use a simple breakdown model such as:

Tickets
Food
Transport

Display total estimated cost prominently.

---

SHARE TRIP LINK

If not already included, add a share button in the trip screen.

Share options:

* Copy link
* Share via social apps

Display a generated link for the trip.

---

DESIGN REQUIREMENTS

Use:

* clean travel-themed color palette
* large destination imagery
* card-based layout
* clear hierarchy
* modern mobile app style

Maintain component consistency across all screens.

Do not redesign existing screens unnecessarily — only enhance or add missing functionality.
